Key Match Events: Tari Eason scored a career-high 27 points in 35 minutes on 11-of-19 shooting.
Eason had three blocks, four steals, and nine rebounds.
Eason had a clutch steal early in the fourth quarter while having five fouls, contributing to Houston's attempted 31-point comeback.
Alperen Sengun had 14 points, 10 rebounds, and four assists in 21 minutes.
Post-Match Reflections: Tari Eason expressed his dislike for the Warriors postgame.
Ime Udoka showed willingness to go deep into the roster to find a way to win.
Others: Houston's shooting struggles continued, shooting 33.3% from three and 41.1% from the field.
